1. cmd: record  (start recording keystrokes)
   <type keystrokes, etc.; can include <ret> chars, other <cmd> line functions
   cmd: -record (stop recording; saves the keystrokes in an unnamed 'current macro'

2.  cmd: play [N] plays the currently defined macro once [or N times]

3.  store X (save the recording in macro named X)

4.  cmd: $X [N] plays macro X once [or N times]





